               <floruit notBefore="1839" notAfter="1860">He was the son of <persName ref="PRS5951Kenfuha">
                     <roleName type="title">
                  daǧǧāmāč</roleName> Kǝnfu Ḫaylu </persName> who ruled <placeName ref="LOC2481Dambey"/> 
                  province from <date>1831</date> until his death in <date>1839</date>.Through him, Gārad Kǝnfu was related to 
                  <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/>. 
                  He is noted as one of the rebels against 
                  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/>, in <placeName ref="LOC2481Dambey"/>
                  and <placeName ref="LOC6186Walqay"/>. In <date>1860</date>, he emerged as as an ally of 
                  <persName ref="PRS7542NeguseW"/>, 
                  at the time he was the most prominent opponent of  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/>. In a skirmish 
                  outside <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar"/>, Gārad killed <persName ref="PRS7907Plowden"/>
               </floruit>
               <death when="1860">He, in turn,  was killed  in revenge by <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/> 
                  in a battle in <placeName ref="LOC6171Waldeb"/> in<date>1860</date>.</death>
            </person>
